{"name": "livechat", "metadata": {"name": "livechat", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: End Users/Desktop", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Natural Language :: English", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Topic :: Communications :: Chat"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pyqt5"], "summary": "A program to display images and gif on other computers within same network.", "upload_time": 1732708324}, "documentation": ["# Python Live Chat  \n\nPython Live Chat is a Python application that allows users to send images and GIFs to selected computers on a local network running the script. The images are displayed in full screen for a specified duration.  \n\n## System Requirements  \n\n- **Windows**: Windows 10, Windows 11 (not tested on earlier versions).  \n- **Linux**: Tested on Xubuntu but should work on other distributions.  \n- **macOS**: Not tested.  \n\n## Requirements  \n\nBefore running the script, ensure you have the required libraries installed. Install them using the following command:  \n```bash\npip install -r requirements.txt  \n```\n\n## Usage  \n\n1. Clone the repository or download the project files.  \n2. Navigate to the project directory.  \n3. Run the application using the following command:  \n\n``` bash\n   python run.pyw  \n```\n\n4. A window will appear, allowing you to:  \n   - **Select connected users**: Users running the script on the same local network are automatically detected and listed as connected.  \n   - **Specify an image or GIF path**: Supports both local file paths and publicly accessible web URLs. Note: URLs requiring authentication will not work.  \n   - **Set the display duration**: Choose how long the image or GIF should remain on the screen.  \n   - Click **Send** to transmit the image or GIF to all selected users.  \n\n## Screenshots  \n\n![Screenshot of Python Live Chat](assets/screenshots/screenshot_0.png)  \n\n---\n\n### Additional Notes  \n\n- **Supported URL types**: Any publicly accessible image URL can be used, provided it doesn't require authentication.  \n- **No duration limit**: There is no restriction on how long an image can be displayed.  \n"], "modules": [{"name": "livechat.receiver", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "livechat.receiver.Receiver", "bases": ["QThread"], "methods": [{"name": "livechat.receiver.Receiver.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "port", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "livechat.receiver.Receiver.run", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "livechat.receiver.Receiver.close", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "livechat.receiver.Receiver.image_received", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "livechat", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "livechat.LiveChat", "xref": {"fqname": "livechat.livechat.LiveChat", "project": null}}, {"name": "livechat.LiveChatWindow", "xref": {"fqname": "livechat.livechat_window.LiveChatWindow", "project": null}}, {"name": "livechat.Popup", "xref": {"fqname": "livechat.popup.Popup", "project": null}}, {"name": "